1
00:00:08,443 --> 00:00:09,966
Previously on Star Trek: Discovery...

2
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:12,360
With the
Enterprise in Spacedock,

3
00:00:12,403 --> 00:00:14,275
Captain Pike and Discovery's mission

4
00:00:14,318 --> 00:00:16,190
to find any rational explanation

5
00:00:16,233 --> 00:00:17,930
for the seven signals
continues to escape me.

6
00:00:17,974 --> 00:00:19,584
And with it, perhaps, any chance

7
00:00:19,628 --> 00:00:21,456
of a relationship with my brother Spock.

8
00:00:21,499 --> 00:00:24,937
Computer, show me Starfleet's
rendering of the seven signals.

9
00:00:24,981 --> 00:00:26,200
Spock drew these signals

10
00:00:26,243 --> 00:00:28,202
two months before they appeared to us.

11
00:00:28,245 --> 00:00:29,681
It's damn near identical.

12
00:00:31,857 --> 00:00:33,555
Amanda?

13
00:00:33,598 --> 00:00:35,470
I stole
Spock's medical file.

14
00:00:35,513 --> 00:00:37,559
I've been waiting for an
update on my officer, Spock.

15
00:00:37,602 --> 00:00:39,430
Your guy is wanted for murder.

16
00:00:39,474 --> 00:00:41,563
Killed three of his doctors,
then fled the starbase.

17
00:00:41,606 --> 00:00:44,000
I thought that he
had left it in the past,

18
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:45,610
but it's back.

19
00:00:45,654 --> 00:00:48,613
- What is it?
- Your brother called it the Red Angel.

20
00:00:48,657 --> 00:00:50,572
That vision changed him forever.

21
00:00:50,615 --> 00:00:52,226
It wasn't because of a vision.

22
00:00:52,269 --> 00:00:55,403
- It was because of me.
- What did you do?

23
00:00:55,446 --> 00:00:56,404
I will find him.

24
00:00:56,447 --> 00:00:58,232
No.

25
00:00:58,275 --> 00:01:00,147
I will.

26
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:03,498
Got it.

27
00:01:03,541 --> 00:01:04,934
After the dark matter hit me...

28
00:01:04,977 --> 00:01:07,763
- It's me.
- I started to see a ghost.

29
00:01:07,806 --> 00:01:09,852
Her name was May, but she's dead. Tilly.

30
00:01:09,895 --> 00:01:11,984
- I am losing, Michael.
- You don't need sickbay.

31
00:01:12,028 --> 00:01:13,812
- You need Stamets.
- We should have results

32
00:01:13,856 --> 00:01:15,118
- in one second.
- There he is.

33
00:01:15,162 --> 00:01:17,251
That's the captain.
That's where he flies.

34
00:01:17,294 --> 00:01:18,774
Just as I suspected.

35
00:01:18,817 --> 00:01:21,733
- You are hosting a eukaryotic organism.
- A fungus?

36
00:01:21,777 --> 00:01:23,996
This might hurt a bit.

37
00:01:30,177 --> 00:01:32,657
Security breach by unknown
alien species in Engineering.

38
00:01:32,701 --> 00:01:35,834
Engage quarantine protocol Alpha-Omega.

39
00:01:39,708 --> 00:01:41,840
Energize.

40
00:01:41,884 --> 00:01:43,103
Teleporter incoming.

41
00:01:56,420 --> 00:01:58,770
- Captain.
- Welcome aboard Discovery, Number One.

42
00:01:58,814 --> 00:02:01,338
The failures cascaded
through all our primaries.

43
00:02:01,382 --> 00:02:04,124
Helm, nav, both impulse and
warp drive. Chief Louvier

44
00:02:04,167 --> 00:02:06,082
has an engineering team
working 'round the clock.

45
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:08,476
I don't think Enterprise will
ever have a chief engineer

46
00:02:08,519 --> 00:02:09,825
more in love with his ship.

47
00:02:09,868 --> 00:02:11,479
Apparently, Enterprise is the only ship

48
00:02:11,522 --> 00:02:13,002
in the fleet that's had any problems.

49
00:02:13,045 --> 00:02:14,134
You know, he warned me.

50
00:02:14,177 --> 00:02:15,657
The damn holographic comm system.

51
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:17,180
Tell Louvier to rip
out the entire system.

52
00:02:17,224 --> 00:02:18,616
From now on we'll communicate

53
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:20,052
using good, old-fashioned view screens.

54
00:02:20,096 --> 00:02:21,663
Truth is I never liked the holograms.

55
00:02:21,706 --> 00:02:23,491
They look too much like ghosts.

56
00:02:23,534 --> 00:02:25,667
He told you I'd say that.

57
00:02:25,710 --> 00:02:27,799
No. I told him.

58
00:02:28,446 --> 00:02:30,584
Cheeseburger. Fries.
Habanero sauce.

59
00:02:30,619 --> 00:02:32,674
You want to order some
lighter fluid with that?

60
00:02:32,717 --> 00:02:33,675
That goes with the shake.

61
00:02:33,718 --> 00:02:36,199
Sorry to keep you in Spacedock.

62
00:02:36,243 --> 00:02:37,635
I've made use of the time, Captain.

63
00:02:37,679 --> 00:02:40,464
You've been looking into the
allegations against Spock.

64
00:02:40,508 --> 00:02:42,858
It's hard to comprehend,
let alone believe,

65
00:02:42,901 --> 00:02:44,642
that he murdered three people

66
00:02:44,686 --> 00:02:47,297
at the psychiatric
facility on Starbase Five.

67
00:02:47,341 --> 00:02:48,342
How's the crew taking it?

68
00:02:48,385 --> 00:02:49,908
They don't know the details.

69
00:02:49,952 --> 00:02:51,432
Only that he's in trouble.

70
00:02:53,347 --> 00:02:55,349
There's something else.

71
00:02:55,392 --> 00:02:57,394
Tell me.

72
00:02:57,438 --> 00:03:01,703
Starfleet's classified
his case Level One.

73
00:03:01,746 --> 00:03:04,184
Line officers don't usually
warrant that kind of scrutiny.

74
00:03:04,227 --> 00:03:06,838
It's unprecedented. Which is
why I've done a little digging.

75
00:03:06,882 --> 00:03:08,100
Sanctioned?

76
00:03:08,144 --> 00:03:10,190
Better you don't know
the answer to that.

77
00:03:10,233 --> 00:03:12,322
Before I look at that,

78
00:03:12,366 --> 00:03:15,717
I need to know why you saw fit
to detour Federation protocols.

79
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:19,329
Something about this
investigation isn't adding up.

80
00:03:19,373 --> 00:03:21,897
I'm not letting him go without a fight.

81
00:03:21,940 --> 00:03:24,204
As usual, we agree.

82
00:03:24,247 --> 00:03:26,597
Captain Pike to the ready room.

83
00:03:26,641 --> 00:03:29,687
I'm late for a briefing.
I'm glad you came.

84
00:03:29,731 --> 00:03:31,254
I'm sorry you can't stay longer.

85
00:03:31,298 --> 00:03:33,256
Next time.

86
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,866
Be careful, Captain.

87
00:03:34,910 --> 00:03:37,217
You, too, Number One.

88
00:03:43,745 --> 00:03:46,051
We should give it a name.

89
00:03:46,095 --> 00:03:47,792
Other than May.

90
00:03:49,098 --> 00:03:52,101
I know it looks like a blob,

91
00:03:52,144 --> 00:03:54,277
but this is one of the most
sophisticated life-forms

92
00:03:54,321 --> 00:03:55,800
I've ever encountered.

93
00:03:55,844 --> 00:03:58,890
It has sentience, intention.

94
00:03:58,934 --> 00:04:02,285
Tilly, the mycelial network
doesn't just connect life.

95
00:04:02,329 --> 00:04:04,113
It contains it.

96
00:04:04,156 --> 00:04:05,506
It's an incubator.

97
00:04:05,549 --> 00:04:08,813
You mean, like, um... like a home?

98
00:04:13,644 --> 00:04:17,257
I've been wondering why
it appeared to me as May,

99
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:18,867
which got me thinking about the real May

100
00:04:18,910 --> 00:04:20,825
that I met when I was, um, 14.

101
00:04:22,349 --> 00:04:25,439
I was, um... I was a weird kid.

102
00:04:25,482 --> 00:04:27,963
You know?
Like, not a lot of friends

103
00:04:28,006 --> 00:04:31,967
and nobody who really
believed in me, including me.

104
00:04:32,010 --> 00:04:35,753
But... she did.

105
00:04:35,797 --> 00:04:40,323
She wanted to connect to
me, and she tried so hard.

106
00:04:40,367 --> 00:04:42,107
But I don't really think

107
00:04:42,151 --> 00:04:43,805
I was the friend to her that she needed.

108
00:04:43,848 --> 00:04:45,415
I'm certain

109
00:04:45,459 --> 00:04:47,983
you were much kinder than
you give yourself credit for.

110
00:04:48,026 --> 00:04:50,333
You always are.

111
00:04:50,377 --> 00:04:52,770
Thank you, but...

112
00:04:52,814 --> 00:04:56,252
I didn't even know she died.

113
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:58,080
I feel like I took her for granted.

114
00:04:58,123 --> 00:05:00,952
That girl who thought I was special.

115
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:03,172
Oh!

116
00:05:07,045 --> 00:05:10,222
I've cross-referenced what
we're calling the Red Angel

117
00:05:10,266 --> 00:05:11,485
with all known winged

118
00:05:11,528 --> 00:05:13,356
and avian life-forms in the Federation.

119
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,662
So far, I've found nothing.

120
00:05:15,924 --> 00:05:17,882
Sorry.

121
00:05:17,926 --> 00:05:20,668
The universal translator
sometimes has trouble

122
00:05:20,711 --> 00:05:23,192
reconfiguring my
lingual clicks and pops.

123
00:05:23,235 --> 00:05:26,500
My answer to you was, "Nothing
in the known universe. "

124
00:05:26,543 --> 00:05:28,502
Which might suggest it's not a species.

125
00:05:28,545 --> 00:05:31,374
- Maybe one of a kind.
- A mutation.

126
00:05:31,418 --> 00:05:33,376
Well, whatever it is,
figuring out how it's connected

127
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:35,726
to these signals will
help us identify it.

128
00:05:35,770 --> 00:05:38,076
If only we knew what it needs.

129
00:05:39,426 --> 00:05:41,689
Commander Nhan, USS Enterprise.

130
00:05:41,732 --> 00:05:42,864
Glad to be here.

131
00:05:42,907 --> 00:05:44,387
Welcome back aboard.

132
00:05:44,431 --> 00:05:45,867
Could you pass the salt?

133
00:05:45,910 --> 00:05:47,695
Commander Saru,

134
00:05:47,738 --> 00:05:49,392
can you shed any light?

135
00:05:49,436 --> 00:05:51,394
My apologies.

136
00:05:51,438 --> 00:05:53,396
I woke up this morning fighting

137
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,050
an acute rhino virus.

138
00:05:55,093 --> 00:05:56,225
So you have a cold.

139
00:05:56,268 --> 00:05:59,750
I had a cold last week, which sucked.

140
00:06:01,012 --> 00:06:03,928
Saurian. Six nasal canals.

141
00:06:03,972 --> 00:06:05,930
It happens to the best of us, Linus.

142
00:06:05,974 --> 00:06:07,932
Everyone to your stations.
Detmer, set a course

143
00:06:07,976 --> 00:06:10,500
for 108 mark four. Maximum warp.

144
00:06:10,544 --> 00:06:11,675
Aye, sir.

145
00:06:11,719 --> 00:06:13,895
Mr. Saru, you look like hell.

146
00:06:13,938 --> 00:06:15,331
You've been burning the
candle at both ends lately.

147
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:16,419
Go get some rest.

148
00:06:16,463 --> 00:06:18,682
As you wish, sir.

149
00:06:18,726 --> 00:06:22,425
Burnham. A word.

150
00:06:22,469 --> 00:06:26,647
I understand your first officer
is on her way to Spacedock.

151
00:06:26,690 --> 00:06:28,649
Was her visit informative?

152
00:06:28,692 --> 00:06:30,302
Number One is very resourceful.

153
00:06:30,346 --> 00:06:33,131
People have a tendency to
end up owing her favors.

154
00:06:33,175 --> 00:06:35,264
She uncovered

155
00:06:35,307 --> 00:06:37,484
some classified information

156
00:06:37,527 --> 00:06:38,702
on Starbase Five.

157
00:06:38,746 --> 00:06:41,139
That is the warp
signature of the shuttle

158
00:06:41,183 --> 00:06:43,359
that Spock stole from
the psychiatric facility.

159
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:45,622
I put us on an intercept course.

160
00:06:45,666 --> 00:06:48,495
We should reach his position
in the next few hours.

161
00:06:53,195 --> 00:06:55,284
S- Sir,

162
00:06:55,327 --> 00:06:57,765
after everything that's happened,

163
00:06:57,808 --> 00:07:01,508
I need to excuse myself
from seeing Spock.

164
00:07:01,551 --> 00:07:03,423
Not sure I follow.

165
00:07:03,466 --> 00:07:05,642
I don't want to make
things worse for him.

166
00:07:05,686 --> 00:07:10,473
He's a fugitive, whatever
the circumstances.

167
00:07:10,517 --> 00:07:14,346
And as Amanda suggested...

168
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:16,610
I'm probably the last person

169
00:07:16,653 --> 00:07:19,482
who should insert
themselves into this problem.

170
00:07:19,526 --> 00:07:22,746
I disagree. He is lost, Captain.

171
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:26,184
You are better suited to help him.

172
00:07:27,795 --> 00:07:30,014
I've thought this through.

173
00:07:30,058 --> 00:07:34,497
Please, trust me.

174
00:07:34,541 --> 00:07:37,500
My abiding trust in you

175
00:07:37,544 --> 00:07:40,155
doesn't eclipse the mission at hand.

176
00:07:40,198 --> 00:07:42,026
Facing whatever happened to Spock,

177
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:44,289
it's not gonna be easy for any of us.

178
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:48,206
Reaching him has to be the priority.

179
00:07:53,647 --> 00:07:55,039
Detmer, status?

180
00:07:55,083 --> 00:07:56,650
Something has grabbed
us out of warp, sir.

181
00:07:56,693 --> 00:07:58,216
Speed dropping to sub-light.

182
00:07:58,260 --> 00:07:59,827
- Helm going unresponsive.
- Shields up.

183
00:07:59,870 --> 00:08:01,132
Red alert. Owosekun,

184
00:08:01,176 --> 00:08:02,177
are we talking tractor beam?

185
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:03,352
More powerful than that, sir.

186
00:08:03,395 --> 00:08:05,223
I'm unable to raise shields.

187
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:08,531
Preliminary analysis indicates
a multiphasic stasis field.

188
00:08:08,575 --> 00:08:10,141
It's disrupting our shield harmonics.

189
00:08:10,185 --> 00:08:11,795
We're at a full stop, sir.

190
00:08:11,839 --> 00:08:14,145
Whatever has us, w-we're
locked into place.

191
00:08:14,189 --> 00:08:15,799
Like a damn fly in a web.

192
00:08:15,843 --> 00:08:18,889
And there is the spider.

193
00:08:29,987 --> 00:08:31,989
♪

194
00:08:59,582 --> 00:09:07,411
